<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-737  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 737.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Data Based Advisor  Nov 1990 v8 n11 p56(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Data Based Solutions 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multi-user database system upgrade offers xBASE memo fieldsupport. (eSoft Inc's The Data Base System 1.1) (The CompleteComdex Catalog 1990) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Esoft Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   The Data Base System 1.1 (Add-in-on software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Add-In-On SoftwareProduct IntroductionData Base Management SystemsMultiuser SoftwareUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Multi-user Database System Upgrade Offers xBASE Memo Field SupportandM;AURORA, CO--eSoft, Inc. announced The Data Base System (tdbs) version 1.1, anupgrade of their multi-user information management system.andP;  tdbs allowstransparent file sharing in multi-user dBASE-compatible applications fromboth remote and local workstations.andP;  This means multiple users can edit thesame files simultaneously.andP;  Version 1.1 also allows integrated memo-fieldediting and supports dBASE-style memo fields.andM;tdbs is designed as an add-on product for eSoft's The Bread Board System(tbbs), which gives up to 32 users simultaneous access to shared files anddata via a single PC.andP;  Another eSoft add-on product, The Integrated MailSystem (tims), is an automated electronic mail server.andM;tdbs 1.1 is priced at $395 for a single-user system.andP;  The 16-user system ispriced at $995, and the 32-user system is priced at $1,795.andP;  For moreinformation, contact eSoft, Inc., (303) 699-6565.andO;</TEXT></DOC>